<br>
Wezloc <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uglasya7.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glasya7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 130<br> <font color=#333333>(5/28/02 6:53:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=218.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We have Valiant Companion....</span><hr size=1> When NPC charms you or your pet, chances are you get a rogue pet that will become an NPC or the pet will just vanish.  NPCs should never be able to charm a pet, it is a pet after all and its the poperty of the PC that summoned it.  There is no real RP reason for allowing NPCs to charm PC pets.<br>
