</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukinelaria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kinelaria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 219<br> <font color=#333333>(5/28/02 9:15:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=218.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We have Valiant Companion....</span><hr size=1> They should make pets uncharmable period, at least till they can fix the problems it can cause. When I've had pets charmed by a mob, I have to camp or zone in order to make a new pet, even though I never seem to get my old pet back even if the mob that charmed it is killed, the pet just goes rogue.<br>
<br>
Kinelaria <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rhasinfirestorm>Rhasin Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 752<br> <font color=#333333>(5/28/02 11:15:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=218.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: We have Valiant Companion....</span><hr size=1> Something I've found which is of extreme duress to me when fighting enchanters (mobs, mostly) is that once YOU (the PC) is charmed, often, it will order you to attack whatever's left attacking it in melee/spells. If you're soloing enchanters, as soon as you do point 1 of damage to your pet, your pet destroys itself, leaving you defenseless and hopefully not a dead man. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=52886">Rhasin Firestorm</A><BR>
Conjurer of the 58th Season<BR>
Prexus</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unilusofheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nilu Sofheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#333333>(5/30/02 5:10:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=218.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   charmable pets...</span><hr size=1> Pets can still be charmed, or at least as of about a month ago...<br>
<br>
     high level group was in ToFS, and we were camping Tserinna.  Tserinna pop'd.  WooHOO!!!  At least it was woohoo, till she charmed my epic pet ( yes, complete with muzzle, BO IV, and full suit of plate armor (summoned) ).  Nastiness at it's finest level..  To add to it, we did CR, and had another peek at her, and lo and behold, she still had my pet charmed.  explain that?  Came back a day later, Tower was empty, and my pet was still guarding her.  Lasted until the next patch.  Needless to say, I don't go to ToFS anymore.<br>
